3.2 Data Visualization
The steps below will be used to generate our Age-Sex pyramid in ggplot2:

Inserting geom_bar() for “Male_SGPopulationranked” and “Female_SGPopulationranked” respectively;
Setting continuous y-axis scale using scale_y_continuous();
Customised a function for the “label” parameter to transform the negative Female population values back to positive;
Customised a function for the “fill” parameter to color maximum population bar as yellow;
Flipping co-ordinates using coord_flip();
Inserting data labels, data source and legends;
Applied facet_wrap to generate plots of the different subset of the data (in this case, the 9 most highly populated Plannng Areas identified);
